{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "sop", "icon": "SOP/voronoifracturepoints", "internal": "voronoifracturepoints", "since": "11.0", "tags": "break", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Voronoi Fracture Points"], "extent": [120, 148]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Given an object and points of impact on the object, this SOP\ngenerates a set of points that can be used as input to the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture", "type": "link", "text": ["Voronoi\nFracture"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture.html"}, " SOP to simulate fracturing the\nobject from those impacts."], "extent": [148, 378]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Voronoi Fracture Points SOP takes two primary inputs: the\npolygonal mesh upon which to generate fracture points, and a set of\npoints which represent ", {"type": "q", "text": ["impacts"]}, " on the mesh.  These impact points can\nbe generated a number of ways, such as through the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/add", "type": "link", "text": ["Add"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/add.html"}, "\nSOP or by ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/scatter", "type": "link", "text": ["scattering"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/scatter.html"}, " points on the surface itself\nor a separate object."], "extent": [378, 741]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This SOP works by generating an impact volume from metaballs copied to\neach impact point.  The second input can also accept metaball\nprimitives directly, which will be merged with any copied metaballs to\nform the impact volume.  This volume is then used to divide the input\nobject into three regions.  "], "extent": [741, 1045]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#surface", "type": "link", "text": ["Surface"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracturepoints.html#surface", "fragment": "#surface"}, " region is the surface of the object where it\nintersects the impact volume.  The ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#interior", "type": "link", "text": ["Interior"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracturepoints.html#interior", "fragment": "#interior"}, " region is the\nintersection of a volume representation of the object and the impact\nvolume. The ", {"scheme": null, "value": "#exterior", "type": "link", "text": ["Exterior"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracturepoints.html#exterior", "fragment": "#exterior"}, " region is the volume of the object\nthat is outside the impact volume."], "extent": [1045, 1356]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["In the following cross-section diagram of a box with a single impact\npoint at the end, the purple wireframe represents the impact volume,\nyellow indicates the surface region, red the interior region, and blue\nthe exterior region."], "extent": [1356, 1587]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": [{"scheme": "Image", "value": "/images/voronoifracturepoints_regions.jpg", "type": "img", "text": ""}], "extent": [1587, 1638]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Each region has parameters that control the density of points\ngenerated within it, and how\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture#clustering", "type": "link", "text": ["clustering"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture.html#clustering", "fragment": "#clustering"}, " should be applied by\na subsequent ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture", "type": "link", "text": ["Voronoi Fracture SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture.html"}, ". A point group is also created for\nthe points generated in each region."], "extent": [1638, 1933]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This SOP serves as a key component in ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/dop/voronoifractureconfigureobject", "type": "link", "text": ["Dynamic\nFracturing"], "fullpath": "/nodes/dop/voronoifractureconfigureobject.html"}, " in DOPs."], "extent": [1933, 2042]}, {"type": "note_group", "body": [{"type": "note", "indent": 0, "role": "item", "extent": [2042, 2048], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": ["This node creates a ", {"type": "q", "text": ["cluster"]}, " attribute on the output points\n      that will only have an effect in fracturing if the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture#clustering", "type": "link", "text": ["Cluster\n      Pieces"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture.html#clustering", "fragment": "#clustering"}, " parameter is enabled\n      on the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Voronoi Fracture"]}, " SOP."], "extent": [2048, 2292]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 1, "id": "inputs", "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2292, 2300], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Geometry for Impact"], "extent": [2300, 2325], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["The polygonal geometry around which to generate the fracture points."], "extent": [2325, 2403]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Impact Points and Metaballs"], "extent": [2403, 2436], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Input points, where each point represents an ", {"type": "q", "text": ["impact"]}, " on the\n        object, and metaballs which are merged to form an impact\n        volume."], "extent": [2436, 2587]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Optional SDF For Depth Sampling"], "extent": [2587, 2624], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["An optional SDF Volume of the object, usually created by\n        ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/isooffset", "type": "link", "text": ["IsoOffset"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/isooffset.html"}, ", used internally in several\n        volume-based operations to generate points in the different\n        volume regions. If not connected, a default one will be\n        created."], "extent": [2624, 2906]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "text": "Inputs"}, {"level": 1, "id": "parameters", "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [2906, 2918], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Impact Radius"], "extent": [2918, 2934], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The radius of the metaball to be copied to each impact point.  "], "extent": [2934, 3007]}, {"type": "tip_group", "body": [{"type": "tip", "indent": 4, "text": [" "], "role": "item", "extent": [3007, 3017], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Each metaball can be transformed by the usual ", {"scheme": null, "value": "/copy/instanceattrs", "type": "link", "text": ["copying attributes"], "fullpath": "/copy/instanceattrs.html"}, " on the impact points."], "extent": [3017, 3135]}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Snap Points to Object"], "extent": [3135, 3158], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 3, "text": ["Snap each impact point to the object before copying."], "extent": [3158, 3215]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Compute Number of Points"], "extent": [3215, 3241], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Calculate the number of points to scatter in each region based on\n    its surface area."], "extent": [3241, 3334]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Points Per Area"], "extent": [3334, 3351], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of points per unit of surface area.  This can be scaled\n    by the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Point Density"]}, " parameter for each region."], "extent": [3351, 3479]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Number of Points"], "extent": [3479, 3497], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The number of points to generate."], "extent": [3497, 3540]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Per Impact"], "extent": [3540, 3552], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Whether the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Number of Points"]}, " parameter specifies the total\n    number of generated points or the number of generated points for\n    each impact point."], "extent": [3552, 3716]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Volume Resolution"], "extent": [3716, 3735], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The resolution of the volume representations of the impact\n    metaballs and the object.  "], "extent": [3735, 3831]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Random Seed"], "extent": [3831, 3844], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The random seed for point scattering."], "extent": [3844, 3891]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Visualize Points"], "extent": [3891, 3909], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["Visualize the generated points. The colors for each region are as\n    follows: yellow/surface, red/interior, blue/exterior."], "extent": [3909, 4042]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}, {"level": 2, "id": "surface", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Surface"], "extent": [4042, 4066], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Point Density"], "extent": [4066, 4082], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The density of point generation for this region.  If ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Compute\n    Number Of Points"]}, " is enabled, this parameter is a multiplier of\n    the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Points Per Area"]}, " value. If an explicit ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Number of Points"]}, "\n    value is specified, this parameter determines the proportion of\n    those points allocated to this region."], "extent": [4082, 4405]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Surface Offset"], "extent": [4405, 4421], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to offset the generated points from the object surface."], "extent": [4421, 4497]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Radius Scale"], "extent": [4497, 4511], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The amount to scale the impact radius before calculating the\n    surface region."], "extent": [4511, 4601]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Clustering"], "extent": [4601, 4613], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use Fracture Settings"], "extent": [4613, 4640], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Create a cluster attribute value of zero for points in this\n        region, allowing a subsequent ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture", "type": "link", "text": ["Voronoi Fracture SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture.html"}, " to override\n        with its own values.  Use the parameters on the Voronoi Fracture SOP to control the size of the clustered pieces."], "extent": [4640, 4928]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Disabled"], "extent": [4928, 4942], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Create a unique cluster attribute value for each point in this\n        region, disabling clustering for every fractured piece\n        subsequently generated."], "extent": [4942, 5108]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Single Piece"], "extent": [5108, 5126], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Create the same cluster value for all points in this region,\n        causing all fractured pieces subsequently generated to be\n        clustered together as a single piece."], "extent": [5126, 5312]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "interior", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Interior"], "extent": [5312, 5338], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Point Density"], "extent": [5338, 5354], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The density of point generation for this region.  If ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Compute\n    Number Of Points"]}, " is enabled, this parameter is a multiplier of\n    the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Points Per Area"]}, " value. If an explicit ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Number of Points"]}, "\n    value is specified, this parameter determines the proportion of\n    those points allocated to this region."], "extent": [5354, 5677]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Clustering"], "extent": [5677, 5689], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use Fracture Settings"], "extent": [5689, 5716], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Create a cluster attribute value of zero for points in this\n        region, allowing a subsequent ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture", "type": "link", "text": ["Voronoi Fracture SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture.html"}, " to override\n        with its own values.  Use the parameters on the Voronoi\n        Fracture SOP to control the size of the clustered pieces."], "extent": [5716, 6012]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Disabled"], "extent": [6012, 6026], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Create a unique cluster attribute value for each point in this\n        region, disabling clustering for every fractured piece\n        subsequently generated."], "extent": [6026, 6192]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Single Piece"], "extent": [6192, 6210], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Create the same cluster value for all points in this region,\n        causing all fractured pieces subsequently generated to be\n        clustered together as a single piece."], "extent": [6210, 6400]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 2, "id": "exterior", "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 0, "text": ["Exterior"], "extent": [6400, 6426], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Point Density"], "extent": [6426, 6442], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The density of point generation for this region.  If ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Compute\n    Number Of Points"]}, " is enabled, this parameter is a multiplier of\n    the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Points Per Area"]}, " value. If an explicit ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Number of Points"]}, "\n    value is specified, this parameter determines the proportion of\n    those points allocated to this region."], "extent": [6442, 6765]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Scatter Location"], "extent": [6765, 6783], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["At Impact"], "extent": [6783, 6798], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Scatter points at the boundary of the Interior and Exterior regions."], "extent": [6798, 6875]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Exterior Volume"], "extent": [6875, 6896], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Scatter points throughout the exterior volume."], "extent": [6896, 6951]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Both"], "extent": [6951, 6961], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Scatter points at both of the above locations."], "extent": [6961, 7025]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Impact Offset"], "extent": [7025, 7040], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 4, "text": ["The offset of the Interior/Exterior boundary when scattering\n    using the ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["At Impact"]}, " or ", {"type": "ui", "text": ["Both"]}, " setting above."], "extent": [7040, 7165]}], "container": true, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 0, "text": ["Clustering"], "extent": [7165, 7177], "body": [{"type": "dt_group", "body": [{"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Use Fracture Settings"], "extent": [7177, 7204], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Create a cluster attribute value of zero for points in this\n        region, allowing a subsequent ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture", "type": "link", "text": ["Voronoi Fracture SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture.html"}, " to override\n        with its own values.  Use the parameters on the Voronoi\n        Fracture SOP to control the size of the clustered pieces."], "extent": [7204, 7500]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Disabled"], "extent": [7500, 7514], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Create a unique cluster attribute value for each point in this\n        region, disabling clustering for every fractured piece\n        subsequently generated."], "extent": [7514, 7680]}], "container": true}, {"type": "dt", "indent": 4, "text": ["Single Piece"], "extent": [7680, 7698], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Create the same cluster value for all points in this region,\n        causing all fractured pieces subsequently generated to be\n        clustered together as a single piece."], "extent": [7698, 7884]}], "container": true}], "container": true}], "container": true, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}], "text": "Parameters"}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [7884, 7893], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture", "type": "link", "text": ["Voronoi Fracture"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture.html"}], "extent": [7893, 7943]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": null, "value": "/dyno/voronoifracture", "type": "link", "text": ["How to control the effects of voronoi fracture"], "fullpath": "/dyno/voronoifracture.html"}], "extent": [7943, 8020]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Voronoi Fracture Points"], "summary": ["Given an object and points of impact on the object, this SOP\ngenerates a set of points that can be used as input to the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture", "type": "link", "text": ["Voronoi\nFracture"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/voronoifracture.html"}, " SOP to simulate fracturing the\nobject from those impacts."]}